{
  "stem": "12289.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a little baby, then, in '44.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I-- I thought it wasn't very wise to keep my family, little family in Budapest facing the arrival of the-- the Soviet troops and the fighting, the fighting between the Germans and the Soviets and all that.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I went home with them, in August '44, and-- and went back on my own.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Going back to your first visit in Budapest, what was the-- the daily life and the contact with the population in Budapest?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was-- it was very-- it was a very normal life, really.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- I-- I had, of course, not been there when the Hungarian first were engaged in the war, when they-- they lost their whole army at the-- at the east front.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, so when I came, they-- they had this very, very sad experience.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So-- and they were quite fed up with-- with the war and all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they tried to-- more or less, to stay out of the fighting and-- and-- and kind of a sabotage on their part.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Of course, they-- they thought they had done then their share, now.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- and they-- they didn't like it very much to-- to go on fighting against the-- It wasn't their war.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They thought it was the Germans' war and all that and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that passivity, of course, in that sense, and the-- the passivity in not persecuting the Jewish people as hard as the Germans wanted, made the Germans invade and occupy, of course, Hungary in March of '44.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had a very good relationship with the Hungarians the whole time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had an old tradition, there, of an embassy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had cultural-- cultural traditions, relationships, and commercial, and political, and so on.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
